      "solution": "s = gets.chomp\n\ndef solve(s)\n  return s.size if s.size < 2\n  return 2 + solve(s[1..-2]) if s[0] == s[-1]\n  last_ix = s.rindex(s[0])\n  [solve(s.drop(1)),\n    case last_ix\n    when 0; 0\n    when 1; 2\n    else 2 + solve(s[1, last_ix - 1])\n    end].max\nend\n\nputs solve(s.chars)",
      "statement": "You are given a string [[s]] consisting of alphanumeric characters and underscores. By removing some characters from the string (but not reordering them), you can create a <<palindrome>>.\n\nYour task is to determine the <<length>> of the <<longest palindrome>> that can be made.\n\nA <<palindrome>> is a string that reads the same backward as forward.\n- Examples: {{a}}, {{aba}}, {{aabbaa}}.\n- Non-examples: {{ab}}, {{abc}}, {{aabbaaa}}.\nCase is important: {{ABBA}} is a palindrome, but {{Abba}} is not.",
